La instruccion es buscar 3 pares de acciones que sean co-integradas

Empezamos con el primer par, Pepsi y CocaCola

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for KO and PEP from Jan 25, 2025 to Feb 27, 2025
start_date = "2025-01-25"
end_date = "2025-02-27"

print("Fetching data for KO...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for PEP...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
ko_prices = ko_data['Close']
pep_prices = pep_data['Close']

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([ko_prices, pep_prices], axis=1).dropna()
ko_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
pep_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

ko_rw = random_walk_simulation(ko_prices.iloc[0], len(ko_prices), scale=5)
pep_rw = random_walk_simulation(pep_prices.iloc[0], len(pep_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

ko_returns = ko_prices.pct_change().dropna()
pep_returns = pep_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(ko_prices, "KO Prices")
unit_root_test(pep_prices, "PEP Prices")
unit_root_test(ko_returns, "KO Returns")
unit_root_test(pep_returns, "PEP Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

ko_arma = fit_arma(ko_returns, "KO Returns")
pep_arma = fit_arma(pep_returns, "PEP Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of KO ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of KO ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of PEP ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of PEP ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between KO and PEP Prices:")
coint_result = coint(ko_prices, pep_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - KO and PEP prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - KO and PEP prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="KO Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_rw, label="KO Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="PEP Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_rw, label="PEP Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(ko_returns.index, ko_returns, label="KO Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_returns.index, pep_returns, label="PEP Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
ko_forecast = ko_arma.forecast(steps=30)
pep_forecast = pep_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=ko_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(ko_returns.index[-30:], ko_returns[-30:], label="KO Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ko_forecast, label="KO ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pep_returns.index[-30:], pep_returns[-30:], label="PEP Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, pep_forecast, label="PEP ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for V and MA from Jan 25, 2025 to Feb 27, 2025
start_date = "2025-01-25"
end_date = "2025-02-27"

print("Fetching data for V...")
v_data = yf.download("V", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for MA...")
ma_data = yf.download("MA", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
v_prices = v_data['Close']
ma_prices = ma_data['Close']

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([v_prices, ma_prices], axis=1).dropna()
v_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
ma_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

v_rw = random_walk_simulation(v_prices.iloc[0], len(v_prices), scale=5)
ma_rw = random_walk_simulation(ma_prices.iloc[0], len(ma_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

v_returns = v_prices.pct_change().dropna()
ma_returns = ma_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(v_prices, "V Prices")
unit_root_test(ma_prices, "MA Prices")
unit_root_test(v_returns, "V Returns")
unit_root_test(ma_returns, "MA Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

v_arma = fit_arma(v_returns, "V Returns")
ma_arma = fit_arma(ma_returns, "MA Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(v_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of V ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(v_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of V ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(ma_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of MA ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(ma_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of MA ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between V and MA Prices:")
coint_result = coint(v_prices, ma_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - V and MA prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - V and MA prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(v_prices.index, v_prices, label="V Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(v_prices.index, v_rw, label="V Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ma_prices.index, ma_prices, label="MA Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(ma_prices.index, ma_rw, label="MA Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(v_returns.index, v_returns, label="V Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(ma_returns.index, ma_returns, label="MA Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
v_forecast = v_arma.forecast(steps=30)
ma_forecast = ma_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=v_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(v_returns.index[-30:], v_returns[-30:], label="V Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, v_forecast, label="V ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ma_returns.index[-30:], ma_returns[-30:], label="MA Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ma_forecast, label="MA ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
